  <title>GLib.mem_set_vtable</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function mem_set_vtable(vtable: <link xref="GLib.MemVTable">GLib.MemVTable</link>): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_mem_set_vtable()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Sets the <link xref="GLib.MemVTable"/> to use for memory allocation. You can use this
to provide custom memory allocation routines.</p>  <p>The <code>vtable</code> only needs to provide malloc(), realloc(), and free()
functions; GLib can provide default implementations of the others.
The malloc() and realloc() implementations should return <code>null</code> on
failure, GLib will handle error-checking for you. <code>vtable</code> is copied,
so need not persist after this function has been called.</p>  <p>Note that this function must be called before using any other GLib
functions.</p>

